solution:
Factor $3^3$ out of the numerator and $3^2$ out of the denominator before subtracting: \[
\frac{3^4-3^3}{3^3-3^2}=\frac{3^3(3-1)}{3^2(3-1)}=\boxed{3}.
\]
model_solution:
## Step 1: Factor out a common term
$\frac{3^4-3^3}{3^3-3^2}=\frac{3^3(3-1)}{3^3(3-1)}$
## Step 2: Simplify the fraction by cancelling out common factors
$\frac{3^3(3-1)}{3^3(3-1)}=\frac{3^3-3^2}{3^2}$
## Step 3: Simplify the fraction
$\frac{3^3-3^2}{3^2}=\frac{27-9}{9}$
## Step 4: 
$\frac{27-9}{9}=\frac{18}{9}$
## Step 5: Simplify the fraction
$\frac{18}{9}=2$
## Step 6: Cancel out the common factor 9 from the numerator and denominator
$\frac{18}{9}=\frac{2}{1}$
$\frac{18}{9}=2$
## Step 6: 
$\frac{18}{9}=2$
$\frac{18}{9} = 2$
$\frac{18}{9}=2$
